This spot of code gunzips Perl source code with a layer pushed on the
parser input.  It's slightly at proof of concept stage, but is a handy
way to run foo.pl.gz files directly, or even to make a
self-uncompressing executable if desired.

The Filter::gunzip home page is

    http://user42.tuxfamily.org/filter-gunzip/index.html
